summary: Confessions of a Jonsa Shipper: I definitely believe that there is some semblance of political Jon at play in season 7....
body:
Confessions of a Jonsa Shipper: I definitely believe that there is some semblance of political Jon at play in season 7. Considering the writing and the acting, political Jon makes a lot of sense to explain Jon’s actions. Also, I know that we should take actors interviews with a grain of salt, but considering the fact that Kit Harrington said that Jon Snow was “kindly manipulating” people in season 7 in a LESSER KNOWN magazine says a lot to me! With that being said even though I do think that some form of political Jon occurred in season 7, I’m still inclined to believe that it wasn’t soely politically motivated that Jon slept with Dany on that boat. Personally I think it was a mixture of three things:

1. Jon knew Dany wanted him and used that to his advantage.

2. The Targeryan incest mojo was on and popping

3. Good old fashion lust.

I’m not really trying to make this a meta but I can see were other factors came into play. I think it’s fair and reasonable assumption that Jon found Dany physically attractive. I also think those Targeryan incest genes were at play. I mean I don’t think it’s a coincidence that we as an audience find out Jon’s “true nature/identity” as a targ as he’s engaging targ-esque like incest. It’s actually pretty hilarious when you think about it! Lol! For me, I personally believe that Jon did sleep with Dany for political reasons(kindly manipulated) but also in a poetic justice way, Jon slept with Dany because he thought had nothing to lose. He thought he couldn’t get her pregnant. (Don’t worry she’s not pregnant people). He thought he could firmly get her on his side and all the while he SUBCONSCIOUSLY thought he could avoid incest with Sansa by sleeping Dany.

But oh how the tables have turned and poor Jon is going to be in for a whirlwind in season 8!

summary: Tyrion geloso di Jon e Daenerys ne Il Trono di Spade? Peter Dinklage: “Il loro amore è pericoloso”
body:
Tyrion geloso di Jon e Daenerys ne Il Trono di Spade? Peter Dinklage: “Il loro amore è pericoloso”

Prima della scena della barca, nessuno si era posto il problema che Tyrion fosse innamorato di Dany. Probabilmente perché nulla, lo faceva pensare.

E mentre sono d'accordo che Tyrion possa fare quella faccia per via della pericolosità della relazione Dany-Jon da un punto di vista politico, rimango dubbiosa sulle motivazioni romantiche.
